title: Adhesives Handbook 3rd ed - J. Shields
description:
Adhesives Handbook 3rd ed - J. Shields (Butterworth, 1985).pdf

Adhesives handbook, Third edition is a guidebook that covers the basic concepts of adhesive bonding process. The book emphasizes products based on advance synthetic polymers. 
The coverage of the text includes design of the adhesive joint; surface preparation of bonding materials; selection of a suitable adhesive; and the specification of processing and testing techniques. 
The book will be of great use to design engineers and technicians involved in the materials bonding process in their respective works
